<DOC><DOCNO> AP880520-0149 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-20-88 1457EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-MortgageDisclosure     05-20 0189</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Mortgage Disclosure,180</SECOND><HEAD>Sandamp;Ls Ordered to Give Clear Explanation of Adjustable RateMortgages</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Savings institutions will be requiredbeginning Oct. 1 to offer prospective borrowers a clear and concisedescription of their adjustable-rate mortgage programs, thegovernment said Friday.   The Federal Home Loan Bank Board, which regulates 3,120federally insured savings institutions, said Sandamp;Ls must provide theinformation either when a mortgage application form is offered orbefore the borrower pays any non-refundable fees, whichever occursfirst.   Lenders must include an historic example of how mortgagepayments would have changed over the past 15 years using the indexor formula on which interest rate changes are based.   Sandamp;Ls must also notify borrowers at least 25 days in advance ofany change in monthly payments.   The new rules were adopted last week and became effectiveMonday, however the bank board did not announce adoption of theregulation until Friday. Sandamp;Ls will have until Oct. 1 to begincomplying.   They are similar to rules for banks and bank holding companiesadopted in December by the Federal Reserve Board and by theComptroller of the Currency in March.</TEXT></DOC>